cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SY 

This paper deals with information processing and information dynamics, which are topics related to information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses neural spiking models, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with complex systems, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
